1
00:00:00,233 --> 00:00:01,166
welcome back

2
00:00:01,166 --> 00:00:03,766
last episode we built a crucible

3
00:00:03,766 --> 00:00:05,666
but couldn't manage to use it

4
00:00:05,866 --> 00:00:08,566
but today it's going to be under the spotlight

5
00:00:08,566 --> 00:00:09,866
or maybe I should say

6
00:00:09,866 --> 00:00:12,233
over the fire that lights up the room

7
00:00:12,666 --> 00:00:13,200
anyways

8
00:00:13,200 --> 00:00:16,800
we prepare it with also some casting channels

9
00:00:17,066 --> 00:00:19,866
then we throw inside it the stuff we want to melt

10
00:00:19,866 --> 00:00:21,500
and unlike the forge

11
00:00:21,500 --> 00:00:24,066
we can do alloys directly inside it

12
00:00:24,400 --> 00:00:25,966
once the metal is liquid

13
00:00:25,966 --> 00:00:29,000
we can pour it inside molds in various ways

14
00:00:29,000 --> 00:00:31,366
which means either with casting channels

15
00:00:31,366 --> 00:00:33,200
or directly in the crucible

16
00:00:33,466 --> 00:00:37,066
the crucible is also big enough to fit our old anvils

17
00:00:37,066 --> 00:00:40,233
thus allowing us to recycle all of our old stuff

18
00:00:40,466 --> 00:00:44,033
but what we actually want to use it for is a blast furnace

19
00:00:44,100 --> 00:00:46,400
and that thing is quite expensive

20
00:00:46,500 --> 00:00:47,100
to build it

21
00:00:47,100 --> 00:00:51,600
we have to break the piggy bank iron ingots we saved up in between episodes

22
00:00:51,600 --> 00:00:54,866
and start hammering those into double iron plates

23
00:00:55,000 --> 00:00:57,400
and after breaking a lot of stone hammers

24
00:00:57,400 --> 00:00:59,833
we managed to craft a blast furnace

25
00:01:00,033 --> 00:01:00,666
however

26
00:01:00,666 --> 00:01:03,300
the controller on its own won't be enough

27
00:01:03,433 --> 00:01:07,300
we also need a lot of fire clay bricks for the rest of the structure

28
00:01:07,300 --> 00:01:10,000
and it was then that we ran out of graphite

29
00:01:10,266 --> 00:01:13,000
thus we went back to our exhausted mine

30
00:01:13,000 --> 00:01:15,633
where with a desperate cinematic action

31
00:01:15,633 --> 00:01:18,400
we found a lot more of what we were looking for

32
00:01:18,533 --> 00:01:20,600
with that we have the stuff we lacked of

33
00:01:20,600 --> 00:01:23,466
and thus managed to build our blast furnace

34
00:01:23,633 --> 00:01:25,766
it is composed by a crucible

35
00:01:25,766 --> 00:01:27,300
the blast furnace on top

36
00:01:27,300 --> 00:01:31,100
and then a chimney of firebricks shielded by iron plates

37
00:01:31,400 --> 00:01:33,600
and we must not forget the bellows

38
00:01:33,800 --> 00:01:35,633
to use our blast furnace

39
00:01:35,633 --> 00:01:37,433
we climb on top of the chimney

40
00:01:37,433 --> 00:01:41,366
and drop in some iron, some coal and some fluxing material

41
00:01:41,466 --> 00:01:45,300
then we turn it on by firing up the mix with a fire starter kit

42
00:01:45,566 --> 00:01:47,833
now we have to wait for it to heat up

43
00:01:47,833 --> 00:01:50,600
adding some charcoal whenever it runs low

44
00:01:50,833 --> 00:01:53,800
once our fuel reaches the maximum temperature

45
00:01:53,800 --> 00:01:54,966
we punch the bellows

46
00:01:54,966 --> 00:01:58,266
to push it to the temperature required for making steel

47
00:01:58,366 --> 00:02:00,433
once the chemical process is done

48
00:02:00,433 --> 00:02:04,633
the molten steel will fall inside the crucible below the blast furnace

49
00:02:04,633 --> 00:02:07,200
where we can retrieve it using molds

50
00:02:07,433 --> 00:02:08,700
to be more precise

51
00:02:08,700 --> 00:02:11,433
what we got from this process is pig iron

52
00:02:11,500 --> 00:02:13,066
to turn it into steel

53
00:02:13,066 --> 00:02:14,566
we have to hammer it quite hard

54
00:02:14,566 --> 00:02:16,366
to get all of the slag out

55
00:02:16,633 --> 00:02:17,633
we keep hammering

56
00:02:17,633 --> 00:02:20,000
until we convert it into high carbon steel

57
00:02:20,000 --> 00:02:21,966
and then into normal steel

58
00:02:22,466 --> 00:02:25,633
and that was the material for our anvil upgrade

59
00:02:26,100 --> 00:02:27,500
but we can do better

60
00:02:27,633 --> 00:02:30,433
we can alloy some other materials into our steel

61
00:02:30,433 --> 00:02:31,833
to make it stronger

62
00:02:31,833 --> 00:02:33,966
and I know this looks like it's weaker

63
00:02:33,966 --> 00:02:36,600
but if we takes this weak steel

64
00:02:36,600 --> 00:02:38,100
weld it with some pig iron

65
00:02:38,100 --> 00:02:39,200
and keep hitting it

66
00:02:39,200 --> 00:02:41,366
we eventually get black steel

67
00:02:41,400 --> 00:02:43,566
which makes for an even better anvil

68
00:02:43,966 --> 00:02:45,766
but we can do even better

69
00:02:45,866 --> 00:02:49,066
we can alloy even more stuff with our different steels

70
00:02:49,066 --> 00:02:50,600
to get blue steel

71
00:02:51,066 --> 00:02:51,766
or

72
00:02:51,766 --> 00:02:52,666
this time

73
00:02:52,666 --> 00:02:55,633
we also have a second equivalent tiered material

74
00:02:55,633 --> 00:02:56,366
red steel

75
00:02:56,366 --> 00:02:58,100
other than the color

76
00:02:58,100 --> 00:03:03,433
the difference between the two is just what kind of extra materials they have in their compound

77
00:03:03,900 --> 00:03:06,633
and to strengthen those two new variants

78
00:03:06,633 --> 00:03:08,433
we have to add some black steel

79
00:03:08,433 --> 00:03:10,300
and keep smashing with our hammer

80
00:03:10,466 --> 00:03:12,600
that means a lot of anvil work

81
00:03:12,633 --> 00:03:15,900
and with that we now have a red steel anvil

82
00:03:16,166 --> 00:03:19,200
this with also blue steel on the same level

83
00:03:19,200 --> 00:03:20,666
is the highest tier

84
00:03:20,666 --> 00:03:24,800
and the thing it will allow us to do is to craft colorful steel buckets

85
00:03:24,800 --> 00:03:27,666
which should be able to withstand the heat from lava

86
00:03:27,966 --> 00:03:29,000
talking of heat

87
00:03:29,000 --> 00:03:32,466
all of that time working next to our forge with hot metals

88
00:03:32,466 --> 00:03:34,700
is giving us heat stroke issues

89
00:03:34,800 --> 00:03:36,900
to avoid getting a too high fever

90
00:03:36,900 --> 00:03:39,966
we shall go outside and take a bath in our pool

91
00:03:40,200 --> 00:03:41,366
after our bath

92
00:03:41,366 --> 00:03:42,600
we can go back to work

93
00:03:42,600 --> 00:03:44,800
where we forge a bucket of the other color

94
00:03:44,966 --> 00:03:45,566
and now

95
00:03:45,566 --> 00:03:49,400
that we have a bucket of each one of the endgame TerraFirm materials

96
00:03:49,400 --> 00:03:52,266
we can merge them together to get the ultimate bucket

97
00:03:52,266 --> 00:03:53,300
the vanilla one

98
00:03:53,500 --> 00:03:54,200
with that

99
00:03:54,200 --> 00:03:57,333
we have completed all of what matter of the primitive age tier

100
00:03:57,333 --> 00:04:00,166
and we are ready to get our factory started

101
00:04:00,366 --> 00:04:03,200
the first machine we will need are the steam ones

102
00:04:03,200 --> 00:04:04,633
and as usual

103
00:04:04,633 --> 00:04:07,366
we shall get a high pressure steam solar boiler

104
00:04:07,700 --> 00:04:10,866
other than avoiding the toxic lead surrounding the silver

105
00:04:10,866 --> 00:04:12,500
we faced a second issue

106
00:04:12,500 --> 00:04:14,366
the purity of our glass

107
00:04:14,733 --> 00:04:19,000
glass we made so far is volcanic due to the black sand we used

108
00:04:19,000 --> 00:04:21,900
that makes it too opaque for a solar boiler

109
00:04:22,066 --> 00:04:25,366
so we went to a not too far river to gather white sand

110
00:04:25,366 --> 00:04:28,233
the only one that makes crystal clear glass

111
00:04:28,566 --> 00:04:32,433
with that we have made our first solar powered boiler

112
00:04:32,666 --> 00:04:34,500
which shall stay on the roof

113
00:04:34,766 --> 00:04:36,633
this machine will need water

114
00:04:36,633 --> 00:04:37,800
and for the moment

115
00:04:37,800 --> 00:04:41,366
the only way we found to do so is to manually insert it

116
00:04:41,633 --> 00:04:43,566
to buffer the produced steam

117
00:04:43,566 --> 00:04:45,700
we can store some in a bronze drum

118
00:04:45,700 --> 00:04:48,200
which will then feed our steam workshop

119
00:04:48,366 --> 00:04:51,066
and our first machine shall be a forge hammer

120
00:04:51,300 --> 00:04:54,800
this machine will basically do most of the anvil jobs

121
00:04:54,866 --> 00:04:55,900
most notably

122
00:04:55,900 --> 00:04:59,366
we get 50% more plates out of our ingots

123
00:04:59,433 --> 00:05:03,700
it can also smash carbon out of iron blooms and high carbon ingots

124
00:05:03,700 --> 00:05:05,666
but that takes a lot of time

125
00:05:05,800 --> 00:05:08,500
our next machine shall be an alloy smelter

126
00:05:08,500 --> 00:05:10,200
followed by a compressor

127
00:05:10,300 --> 00:05:11,366
a macerator

128
00:05:11,600 --> 00:05:14,866
and finally after making a little bit more of room

129
00:05:14,866 --> 00:05:16,033
an extractor

130
00:05:16,166 --> 00:05:19,033
the next step in our progression is to make rubber

131
00:05:19,300 --> 00:05:23,300
that requires some resin which is made by kapok, a tropical tree

132
00:05:23,300 --> 00:05:27,033
which we already brought back home from the kaolinite clay trip

133
00:05:27,033 --> 00:05:28,666
to extract it resin

134
00:05:28,666 --> 00:05:30,800
we could put its wood in an extractor

135
00:05:30,866 --> 00:05:33,600
but a better way is to extract it with a tap

136
00:05:33,800 --> 00:05:35,966
filling up a whole bucket with this stuff

137
00:05:35,966 --> 00:05:38,100
will take enough time to make us question

138
00:05:38,100 --> 00:05:41,433
if using a steam machine would have been a better option

139
00:05:41,433 --> 00:05:43,400
but we use this meditation time to

140
00:05:43,400 --> 00:05:45,700
instead look for better stuff to do

141
00:05:45,766 --> 00:05:48,433
thus we started working on making some gears

142
00:05:48,433 --> 00:05:50,300
to expand our workshop

143
00:05:50,400 --> 00:05:51,866
and to make those spin

144
00:05:51,866 --> 00:05:54,266
we shall use the iconic water well

145
00:05:54,400 --> 00:05:56,966
now that we have achieved kinetic energy

146
00:05:56,966 --> 00:06:00,300
we can power a press to increase our plate yield

147
00:06:00,433 --> 00:06:02,300
the process is quite slow

148
00:06:02,300 --> 00:06:05,766
so we add some gears to speed up the process

149
00:06:05,900 --> 00:06:07,733
for more advanced machines

150
00:06:07,733 --> 00:06:09,666
we will need electron tubes

151
00:06:10,100 --> 00:06:11,400
the main issue here is that

152
00:06:11,400 --> 00:06:13,400
we will be needing a lot of resin

153
00:06:13,766 --> 00:06:17,166
so we go back to our latex collection process

154
00:06:17,433 --> 00:06:20,000
to process it we need some sulfur

155
00:06:20,000 --> 00:06:23,800
but the main issue is finding a way that is easy to automate

156
00:06:24,066 --> 00:06:26,700
and of that seems to be the best choice

157
00:06:26,833 --> 00:06:28,966
it also uses less sulfur

158
00:06:29,166 --> 00:06:31,800
the issue is that it is made with wax

159
00:06:31,900 --> 00:06:35,300
so we built some beehives in a field of flowers

160
00:06:35,433 --> 00:06:37,433
usually it takes some weeks

161
00:06:37,433 --> 00:06:38,300
but we got lucky

162
00:06:38,300 --> 00:06:41,700
and managed to attract two bees in a couple of days

163
00:06:41,766 --> 00:06:44,100
we retrieve the wax and build the vat

164
00:06:44,200 --> 00:06:46,233
but since we can't automate it

165
00:06:46,233 --> 00:06:48,400
we shall buffer latex with a drum

166
00:06:48,500 --> 00:06:51,200
next we manually place it in the vat

167
00:06:51,200 --> 00:06:53,600
add the sulfur and let it process

168
00:06:53,700 --> 00:06:56,166
since that was taking too much time

169
00:06:56,166 --> 00:06:58,266
we also use the pot recipe

170
00:06:58,500 --> 00:07:00,933
and since that one was slow too

171
00:07:00,933 --> 00:07:02,266
we made more pots

172
00:07:02,500 --> 00:07:04,166
and this is when we realized

173
00:07:04,166 --> 00:07:06,466
we should have placed the vat above the fire

174
00:07:06,766 --> 00:07:08,166
now that we have resin

175
00:07:08,166 --> 00:07:13,100
it's just a matter of smaller easier tasks before we can get the electron tube

176
00:07:13,400 --> 00:07:15,833
we use those to craft some deployers

177
00:07:15,833 --> 00:07:19,033
so that we can start assembling vacuum tubes

178
00:07:19,300 --> 00:07:22,600
those are part of our next major progress breakthrough

179
00:07:22,600 --> 00:07:24,200
electric circuits

180
00:07:24,433 --> 00:07:26,133
but before we get there

181
00:07:26,133 --> 00:07:28,266
we have one more major issue

182
00:07:28,266 --> 00:07:29,066
rubber

183
00:07:29,100 --> 00:07:31,600
we can easily get it from working resin

184
00:07:31,600 --> 00:07:33,433
but we are not making enough

185
00:07:33,666 --> 00:07:35,666
and to make thing worse

186
00:07:35,666 --> 00:07:39,233
our production is soon going to halt for a couple of months

187
00:07:39,366 --> 00:07:42,633
so we instead opt for extracting the logs

188
00:07:42,700 --> 00:07:45,033
this means we will need even more wood

189
00:07:45,133 --> 00:07:47,000
while we can easily gather it

190
00:07:47,000 --> 00:07:48,000
I think manually

191
00:07:48,000 --> 00:07:51,766
collecting it is a barbaric thing to do with our current technology

192
00:07:51,966 --> 00:07:53,700
to automate such task

193
00:07:53,700 --> 00:07:56,833
we start by getting a source of perpetual motion

194
00:07:57,100 --> 00:07:59,033
and we need some solid structure

195
00:07:59,033 --> 00:08:01,033
to prevent the dirt from breaking it

196
00:08:01,300 --> 00:08:04,833
now that we have a spinning block surrounded by a nice field

197
00:08:04,833 --> 00:08:06,200
we build a long arm

198
00:08:06,200 --> 00:08:08,633
that will support the tools for chopping trees

199
00:08:08,633 --> 00:08:10,266
and planting new ones

200
00:08:10,666 --> 00:08:14,266
we add a system to manage the extraction of the collected wood

201
00:08:14,700 --> 00:08:15,133
finally

202
00:08:15,133 --> 00:08:18,066
we glue everything into a single chunky machine

203
00:08:18,066 --> 00:08:20,800
and connect the missing shaft to make it work

204
00:08:21,066 --> 00:08:22,200
and there we have it

205
00:08:22,400 --> 00:08:24,300
our automated tree farm

206
00:08:24,566 --> 00:08:27,300
for trees to grow it will take some time

207
00:08:27,300 --> 00:08:28,400
in the meanwhile

208
00:08:28,400 --> 00:08:30,233
we can work with what we already have

209
00:08:30,233 --> 00:08:32,433
to get some rubber to get started

210
00:08:32,666 --> 00:08:37,600
and while this was the last material preventing us from making LV circuits

211
00:08:37,600 --> 00:08:40,233
we don't have enough resin for making enough

212
00:08:40,466 --> 00:08:41,633
and the main issue is that

213
00:08:41,633 --> 00:08:45,100
we won't be able to make any more for the next 3 months

214
00:08:45,166 --> 00:08:50,900
we can spend this time by playing minesweeper between the toxic ores and the falling rocks

215
00:08:50,966 --> 00:08:52,866
and as you probably noticed

216
00:08:52,866 --> 00:08:54,633
we are looking for silver

217
00:08:54,666 --> 00:08:57,233
so that we can expand our solar boiler farm

218
00:08:57,233 --> 00:08:59,366
to power our growing automation

219
00:08:59,700 --> 00:09:01,600
however it is now winter

220
00:09:01,600 --> 00:09:04,666
and our automation decided to go on vacation

221
00:09:04,800 --> 00:09:06,766
we use that time to go warm up

222
00:09:06,766 --> 00:09:08,966
by doing some manual work

223
00:09:09,100 --> 00:09:09,300
but

224
00:09:09,300 --> 00:09:12,633
working like that is giving us the wrong kind of sweat

225
00:09:12,766 --> 00:09:13,500
so

226
00:09:13,500 --> 00:09:16,900
after getting cold sweats in the jellied winter caves

227
00:09:16,900 --> 00:09:20,200
we go work in the hot sauna of our blast furnace

228
00:09:20,433 --> 00:09:24,033
and after the great sadness of manually pouring out ingots

229
00:09:24,033 --> 00:09:26,466
we figured out a better way of doing it

230
00:09:26,700 --> 00:09:31,000
we cool down the white hot steel by making it move through a copper pump

231
00:09:31,000 --> 00:09:31,633
with that

232
00:09:31,633 --> 00:09:34,766
we can easily work iron in all of its forms

233
00:09:34,866 --> 00:09:39,233
we spend the rest of the winter stacking up ingots over ingots over ingots of it

234
00:09:39,233 --> 00:09:43,100
until it is time to put it to good use during the upcoming spring

235
00:09:43,100 --> 00:09:46,600
while that steel is enough for many LV machine hulls

236
00:09:46,600 --> 00:09:49,966
we are limited by other materials such as red steel

237
00:09:50,033 --> 00:09:52,833
for now we can only make four hulls

238
00:09:52,866 --> 00:09:56,466
and this was just the easy part of LV machines

239
00:09:56,466 --> 00:09:58,066
now that it's February

240
00:09:58,066 --> 00:10:01,766
the latex started dripping out of the kapok trees again

241
00:10:01,800 --> 00:10:03,366
we quickly gathers lots of it

242
00:10:03,366 --> 00:10:06,033
and boil it with some sulfur to obtain resin

243
00:10:06,033 --> 00:10:09,866
which we can use to make the resistors and circuit boards we were lacking of

244
00:10:09,866 --> 00:10:12,633
for the next thing we needed for the LV tier

245
00:10:12,700 --> 00:10:14,300
electric circuits

246
00:10:14,366 --> 00:10:15,866
now that we have those

247
00:10:15,866 --> 00:10:18,500
we just have to quickly craft a bunch of motors

248
00:10:18,500 --> 00:10:20,466
to unlock the LV tier

249
00:10:20,566 --> 00:10:23,400
and since this is going to be a whole new age

250
00:10:23,400 --> 00:10:26,033
I think we can close this episode here

251
00:10:26,233 --> 00:10:27,166
bye bye

252
00:00:00,233 --> 00:00:01,166
欢迎回来

253
00:00:01,166 --> 00:00:03,766
上一集我们做了坩埚

254
00:00:03,766 --> 00:00:05,666
但还没能真正用起来

255
00:00:05,866 --> 00:00:08,566
不过今天它就是主角

256
00:00:08,566 --> 00:00:09,866
或者该说

257
00:00:09,866 --> 00:00:12,233
是在照亮房间的火焰上方当主角

258
00:00:12,666 --> 00:00:13,200
总之

259
00:00:13,200 --> 00:00:16,800
我们先把它和浇铸槽道一起准备好

260
00:00:17,066 --> 00:00:19,866
再把要熔化的材料丢进去

261
00:00:19,866 --> 00:00:21,500
而且和锻造炉不同

262
00:00:21,500 --> 00:00:24,066
我们可以直接在里面做合金

263
00:00:24,400 --> 00:00:25,966
金属变成液态后

264
00:00:25,966 --> 00:00:29,000
就能用多种方式把它浇进模具

265
00:00:29,000 --> 00:00:31,366
也就是要么走浇铸槽道

266
00:00:31,366 --> 00:00:33,200
要么直接在坩埚里浇

267
00:00:33,466 --> 00:00:37,066
坩埚也够大，能放进旧铁砧

268
00:00:37,066 --> 00:00:40,233
这样就能回收所有旧装备

269
00:00:40,466 --> 00:00:44,033
但我们真正想用它做的是高炉

270
00:00:44,100 --> 00:00:46,400
而那玩意相当贵

271
00:00:46,500 --> 00:00:47,100
要造它

272
00:00:47,100 --> 00:00:51,600
得把两集之间攒下的铁锭存款全砸了

273
00:00:51,600 --> 00:00:54,866
开始把它们锤成双层铁板

274
00:00:55,000 --> 00:00:57,400
砸坏一堆石锤之后

275
00:00:57,400 --> 00:00:59,833
我们终于把高炉控制器做出来了

276
00:01:00,033 --> 00:01:00,666
不过

277
00:01:00,666 --> 00:01:03,300
光有控制器还不够

278
00:01:03,433 --> 00:01:07,300
结构其他部分还要大量耐火黏土砖

279
00:01:07,300 --> 00:01:10,000
然后我们石墨刚好用光

280
00:01:10,266 --> 00:01:13,000
于是又回到被榨干的矿洞

281
00:01:13,000 --> 00:01:15,633
经过一段绝望的电影式操作

282
00:01:15,633 --> 00:01:18,400
终于又找到了很多目标矿

283
00:01:18,533 --> 00:01:20,600
这下缺的材料补齐了

284
00:01:20,600 --> 00:01:23,466
总算把高炉搭起来

285
00:01:23,633 --> 00:01:25,766
它由下方坩埚组成

286
00:01:25,766 --> 00:01:27,300
上面是高炉本体

287
00:01:27,300 --> 00:01:31,100
再往上是铁板包裹的耐火砖烟囱

288
00:01:31,400 --> 00:01:33,600
还有别忘了风箱

289
00:01:33,800 --> 00:01:35,633
使用高炉时

290
00:01:35,633 --> 00:01:37,433
我们爬到烟囱顶

291
00:01:37,433 --> 00:01:41,366
往里投铁、煤和助熔剂

292
00:01:41,466 --> 00:01:45,300
再用引火套件把混合物点燃启动

293
00:01:45,566 --> 00:01:47,833
接下来等它升温

294
00:01:47,833 --> 00:01:50,600
燃料不足就补木炭

295
00:01:50,833 --> 00:01:53,800
等燃料达到最高温

296
00:01:53,800 --> 00:01:54,966
就去猛按风箱

297
00:01:54,966 --> 00:01:58,266
把温度推到炼钢所需区间

298
00:01:58,366 --> 00:02:00,433
化学过程完成后

299
00:02:00,433 --> 00:02:04,633
熔融钢液会落入高炉下方的坩埚

300
00:02:04,633 --> 00:02:07,200
我们再用模具取出

301
00:02:07,433 --> 00:02:08,700
更准确地说

302
00:02:08,700 --> 00:02:11,433
这一流程先产出的是生铁

303
00:02:11,500 --> 00:02:13,066
要变成钢

304
00:02:13,066 --> 00:02:14,566
得狠狠锤

305
00:02:14,566 --> 00:02:16,366
把里面的渣打出来

306
00:02:16,633 --> 00:02:17,633
持续锤打

307
00:02:17,633 --> 00:02:20,000
直到它变成高碳钢

308
00:02:20,000 --> 00:02:21,966
再变成普通钢

309
00:02:22,466 --> 00:02:25,633
这就是升级铁砧的材料

310
00:02:26,100 --> 00:02:27,500
但还可以更进一步

311
00:02:27,633 --> 00:02:30,433
我们还能往钢里加别的材料做合金

312
00:02:30,433 --> 00:02:31,833
让它更强

313
00:02:31,833 --> 00:02:33,966
我知道看起来像更弱了

314
00:02:33,966 --> 00:02:36,600
但如果把这种“弱钢”

315
00:02:36,600 --> 00:02:38,100
和生铁焊在一起

316
00:02:38,100 --> 00:02:39,200
再继续猛锤

317
00:02:39,200 --> 00:02:41,366
最终会得到黑钢

318
00:02:41,400 --> 00:02:43,566
它能做更好的铁砧

319
00:02:43,966 --> 00:02:45,766
但还能更好

320
00:02:45,866 --> 00:02:49,066
我们可以继续给不同钢种加更多合金

321
00:02:49,066 --> 00:02:50,600
做出蓝钢

322
00:02:51,066 --> 00:02:51,766
或者

323
00:02:51,766 --> 00:02:52,666
这次还有

324
00:02:52,666 --> 00:02:55,633
另一个同级材料

325
00:02:55,633 --> 00:02:56,366
红钢

326
00:02:56,366 --> 00:02:58,100
除了颜色外

327
00:02:58,100 --> 00:03:03,433
它俩差别只在配方里额外材料不同

328
00:03:03,900 --> 00:03:06,633
要强化这两种新钢

329
00:03:06,633 --> 00:03:08,433
还得加入一些黑钢

330
00:03:08,433 --> 00:03:10,300
然后继续开锤

331
00:03:10,466 --> 00:03:12,600
也就是又一大堆铁砧活

332
00:03:12,633 --> 00:03:15,900
这样我们就有了红钢铁砧

333
00:03:16,166 --> 00:03:19,200
它和蓝钢铁砧

334
00:03:19,200 --> 00:03:20,666
同属最高等级

335
00:03:20,666 --> 00:03:24,800
能做的关键东西是彩色钢桶

336
00:03:24,800 --> 00:03:27,666
理论上可承受熔岩高温

337
00:03:27,966 --> 00:03:29,000
说到高温

338
00:03:29,000 --> 00:03:32,466
我们长期在锻炉旁打热金属

339
00:03:32,466 --> 00:03:34,700
已经有点中暑迹象

340
00:03:34,800 --> 00:03:36,900
为了别烧到高烧

341
00:03:36,900 --> 00:03:39,966
得出去泡个水降温

342
00:03:40,200 --> 00:03:41,366
泡完澡

343
00:03:41,366 --> 00:03:42,600
就能回来继续干活

344
00:03:42,600 --> 00:03:44,800
先锻另一个颜色的钢桶

345
00:03:44,966 --> 00:03:45,566
现在

346
00:03:45,566 --> 00:03:49,400
我们已经有了TerraFirma终局两种材料桶

347
00:03:49,400 --> 00:03:52,266
把它们合在一起

348
00:03:52,266 --> 00:03:53,300
就得到终极桶

349
00:03:53,500 --> 00:03:54,200
也就是原版铁桶

350
00:03:54,200 --> 00:03:57,333
到这一步

351
00:03:57,333 --> 00:04:00,166
原始时代阶段该做的都做完了

352
00:04:00,366 --> 00:04:03,200
可以正式开工厂了

353
00:04:03,200 --> 00:04:04,633
首先要上的机器是蒸汽机

354
00:04:04,633 --> 00:04:07,366
和之前一样

355
00:04:07,700 --> 00:04:10,866
我们先做高压太阳能蒸汽锅炉

356
00:04:10,866 --> 00:04:12,500
除了要避开银矿周围有毒铅矿

357
00:04:12,500 --> 00:04:14,366
还遇到第二个问题

358
00:04:14,733 --> 00:04:19,000
玻璃纯度不够

359
00:04:19,000 --> 00:04:21,900
之前用黑沙烧的是火山玻璃

360
00:04:22,066 --> 00:04:25,366
对太阳能锅炉来说太不透光

361
00:04:25,366 --> 00:04:28,233
所以去不远处河边挖白沙

362
00:04:28,566 --> 00:04:32,433
只有它能烧出通透玻璃

363
00:04:32,666 --> 00:04:34,500
有了这个就做出第一台太阳能锅炉

364
00:04:34,766 --> 00:04:36,633
它会放在屋顶

365
00:04:36,633 --> 00:04:37,800
机器需要供水

366
00:04:37,800 --> 00:04:41,366
目前我们找到的办法只有手动加水

367
00:04:41,633 --> 00:04:43,566
为了缓存产出的蒸汽

368
00:04:43,566 --> 00:04:45,700
可以先存进一个青铜桶

369
00:04:45,700 --> 00:04:48,200
再去喂蒸汽车间

370
00:04:48,366 --> 00:04:51,066
第一台机器做锻造锤

371
00:04:51,300 --> 00:04:54,800
这机器基本能替代大部分铁砧工序

372
00:04:54,866 --> 00:04:55,900
最重要的是

373
00:04:55,900 --> 00:04:59,366
每个锭打板能多出50%产量

374
00:04:59,433 --> 00:05:03,700
也能把铁团和高碳锭里的碳砸出来

375
00:05:03,700 --> 00:05:05,666
但这个过程很慢

376
00:05:05,800 --> 00:05:08,500
下一台做合金炉

377
00:05:08,500 --> 00:05:10,200
然后是压缩机

378
00:05:10,300 --> 00:05:11,366
粉碎机

379
00:05:11,600 --> 00:05:14,866
最后腾出一点空间后

380
00:05:14,866 --> 00:05:16,033
再做提取机

381
00:05:16,166 --> 00:05:19,033
接下来推进目标是橡胶

382
00:05:19,300 --> 00:05:23,300
需要树脂，而树脂来自热带木棉树

383
00:05:23,300 --> 00:05:27,033
这树我们在高岭土之旅时已经带回来了

384
00:05:27,033 --> 00:05:28,666
要提取树脂

385
00:05:28,666 --> 00:05:30,800
可以把木棉木头丢进提取机

386
00:05:30,866 --> 00:05:33,600
但更好的办法是用树脂龙头直接采

387
00:05:33,800 --> 00:05:35,966
采满整整一桶

388
00:05:35,966 --> 00:05:38,100
慢到让人怀疑

389
00:05:38,100 --> 00:05:41,433
还不如用蒸汽机直接跑

390
00:05:41,433 --> 00:05:43,400
不过这段“冥想时间”里

391
00:05:43,400 --> 00:05:45,700
我们决定找点更值的事做

392
00:05:45,766 --> 00:05:48,433
于是开始做齿轮

393
00:05:48,433 --> 00:05:50,300
扩建车间

394
00:05:50,400 --> 00:05:51,866
而要让它们转起来

395
00:05:51,866 --> 00:05:54,266
我们用了经典水车井

396
00:05:54,400 --> 00:05:56,966
现在有了动能

397
00:05:56,966 --> 00:06:00,300
就能带动压板机提升板材产量

398
00:06:00,433 --> 00:06:02,300
过程还是偏慢

399
00:06:02,300 --> 00:06:05,766
所以又加了几组齿轮提速

400
00:06:05,900 --> 00:06:07,733
要做更高级机器

401
00:06:07,733 --> 00:06:09,666
还需要电子管

402
00:06:10,100 --> 00:06:11,400
最大问题在于

403
00:06:11,400 --> 00:06:13,400
我们需要大量树脂

404
00:06:13,766 --> 00:06:17,166
所以又回到采乳胶流程

405
00:06:17,433 --> 00:06:20,000
处理乳胶需要硫

406
00:06:20,000 --> 00:06:23,800
真正难点是找一条好自动化的工艺

407
00:06:24,066 --> 00:06:26,700
其中这一条看起来最优

408
00:06:26,833 --> 00:06:28,966
还能更省硫

409
00:06:29,166 --> 00:06:31,800
但它需要蜂蜡

410
00:06:31,900 --> 00:06:35,300
于是我们在花田里摆了蜂箱

411
00:06:35,433 --> 00:06:37,433
正常要等几周

412
00:06:37,433 --> 00:06:38,300
但这次运气不错

413
00:06:38,300 --> 00:06:41,700
几天就引来了两只蜜蜂

414
00:06:41,766 --> 00:06:44,100
拿到蜂蜡后做出反应槽

415
00:06:44,200 --> 00:06:46,233
但因为还没法自动化

416
00:06:46,233 --> 00:06:48,400
先用桶缓存乳胶

417
00:06:48,500 --> 00:06:51,200
再手动灌进反应槽

418
00:06:51,200 --> 00:06:53,600
加硫磺让它反应

419
00:06:53,700 --> 00:06:56,166
因为还是太慢

420
00:06:56,166 --> 00:06:58,266
也同时跑锅煮配方

421
00:06:58,500 --> 00:07:00,933
结果那条也慢

422
00:07:00,933 --> 00:07:02,266
于是我们又多做了几口锅

423
00:07:02,500 --> 00:07:04,166
这时才意识到

424
00:07:04,166 --> 00:07:06,466
反应槽本该架在火上

425
00:07:06,766 --> 00:07:08,166
现在树脂有了

426
00:07:08,166 --> 00:07:13,100
接下来就是一串小任务，做出电子管

427
00:07:13,400 --> 00:07:15,833
我们先用它做部署器

428
00:07:15,833 --> 00:07:19,033
这样就能开始组装真空管

429
00:07:19,300 --> 00:07:22,600
它们是下一次大突破的核心材料之一

430
00:07:22,600 --> 00:07:24,200
电路

431
00:07:24,433 --> 00:07:26,133
但在那之前

432
00:07:26,133 --> 00:07:28,266
还有一个大问题

433
00:07:28,266 --> 00:07:29,066
橡胶

434
00:07:29,100 --> 00:07:31,600
虽然树脂加工能稳定出橡胶

435
00:07:31,600 --> 00:07:33,433
但产量还是不够

436
00:07:33,666 --> 00:07:35,666
更糟的是

437
00:07:35,666 --> 00:07:39,233
接下来几个月产线还会停摆

438
00:07:39,366 --> 00:07:42,633
所以我们改走提取原木路线

439
00:07:42,700 --> 00:07:45,033
这意味着还要更多木材

440
00:07:45,133 --> 00:07:47,000
木头当然能手砍

441
00:07:47,000 --> 00:07:48,000
但说实话

442
00:07:48,000 --> 00:07:51,766
以现在的科技手砍太原始了

443
00:07:51,966 --> 00:07:53,700
要把这件事自动化

444
00:07:53,700 --> 00:07:56,833
先从拿到“永动”动力源开始

445
00:07:57,100 --> 00:07:59,033
还得有足够坚固的结构

446
00:07:59,033 --> 00:08:01,033
防止泥土把装置搞坏

447
00:08:01,300 --> 00:08:04,833
现在有了被农田包围的旋转动力块

448
00:08:04,833 --> 00:08:06,200
我们搭了一条长机械臂

449
00:08:06,200 --> 00:08:08,633
用来挂砍树工具

450
00:08:08,633 --> 00:08:10,266
以及补种工具

451
00:08:10,666 --> 00:08:14,266
再加一套收集木材的抽取系统

452
00:08:14,700 --> 00:08:15,133
最后

453
00:08:15,133 --> 00:08:18,066
把这些全拼成一台大机器

454
00:08:18,066 --> 00:08:20,800
接上缺的传动轴让它运转

455
00:08:21,066 --> 00:08:22,200
成了

456
00:08:22,400 --> 00:08:24,300
自动树场上线

457
00:08:24,566 --> 00:08:27,300
树木长成还要时间

458
00:08:27,300 --> 00:08:28,400
在这期间

459
00:08:28,400 --> 00:08:30,233
先用手头存货

460
00:08:30,233 --> 00:08:32,433
做一批起步橡胶

461
00:08:32,666 --> 00:08:37,600
虽然这是卡我们LV电路的最后一种材料

462
00:08:37,600 --> 00:08:40,233
但树脂数量依旧不够

463
00:08:40,466 --> 00:08:41,633
更关键的是

464
00:08:41,633 --> 00:08:45,100
未来三个月都几乎没法继续产树脂

465
00:08:45,166 --> 00:08:50,900
这段时间就去矿里玩“扫雷”

466
00:08:50,966 --> 00:08:52,866
你应该也看出来了

467
00:08:52,866 --> 00:08:54,633
我们在找银

468
00:08:54,666 --> 00:08:57,233
为了扩建太阳能锅炉阵列

469
00:08:57,233 --> 00:08:59,366
给不断扩张的自动化供能

470
00:08:59,700 --> 00:09:01,600
但现在是冬天

471
00:09:01,600 --> 00:09:04,666
自动化产线直接“休假”

472
00:09:04,800 --> 00:09:06,766
我们就趁这时间去热热身

473
00:09:06,766 --> 00:09:08,966
做些手工活

474
00:09:09,100 --> 00:09:09,300
但是

475
00:09:09,300 --> 00:09:12,633
这种干法只会出一身不对劲的汗

476
00:09:12,766 --> 00:09:13,500
所以

477
00:09:13,500 --> 00:09:16,900
在冰冷洞穴里冒完冷汗后

478
00:09:16,900 --> 00:09:20,200
我们回到高炉“桑拿房”继续干

479
00:09:20,433 --> 00:09:24,033
经历了手动浇锭的大悲伤之后

480
00:09:24,033 --> 00:09:26,466
终于想出更好的办法

481
00:09:26,700 --> 00:09:31,000
让白热钢液通过铜泵流动来冷却

482
00:09:31,000 --> 00:09:31,633
这样一来

483
00:09:31,633 --> 00:09:34,766
各种形态的铁都能轻松处理

484
00:09:34,866 --> 00:09:39,233
整个冬天我们都在疯狂囤锭

485
00:09:39,233 --> 00:09:43,100
就等春天到来好好开工

486
00:09:43,100 --> 00:09:46,600
这些钢虽然够做不少LV机器外壳

487
00:09:46,600 --> 00:09:49,966
但仍被红钢等材料卡着

488
00:09:50,033 --> 00:09:52,833
目前最多只能做4个机壳

489
00:09:52,866 --> 00:09:56,466
而这还只是LV机器最简单的部分

490
00:09:56,466 --> 00:09:58,066
到了二月

491
00:09:58,066 --> 00:10:01,766
木棉树又开始滴乳胶

492
00:10:01,800 --> 00:10:03,366
我们迅速采了一大堆

493
00:10:03,366 --> 00:10:06,033
加硫煮成树脂

494
00:10:06,033 --> 00:10:09,866
用来补齐短缺的电阻和电路板

495
00:10:09,866 --> 00:10:12,633
也就是LV阶段下一项关键材料

496
00:10:12,700 --> 00:10:14,300
电路

497
00:10:14,366 --> 00:10:15,866
现在材料齐了

498
00:10:15,866 --> 00:10:18,500
只要再快速做一批马达

499
00:10:18,500 --> 00:10:20,466
就能解锁LV阶段

500
00:10:20,566 --> 00:10:23,400
既然这是一个全新时代的开端

501
00:10:23,400 --> 00:10:26,033
这集就先到这里

502
00:10:26,233 --> 00:10:27,166
拜拜

